snippet.textDisplay:
An unofficial translation: 

Hold the helm for but a moment.
And steady my boat; 
For with you as a helmsman,
Even storms change course.

Do keep watch over me,
To see my life get better;
And I’ll tell my troubles,
To retreat from afar.

Sing me a song, oh boatman!
And lull me to sweet slumber.
And before the break of dawn,
Take me to my destination.
